07/10/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Parliament overwhelmingly approved on Tuesday (October 6th) a government proposal to extend the army's mandate to conduct cross-border operations against the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in northern Iraq. The current deadline was to expire on October 17th. 
In other news, Turkish President Abdullah Gul kicks off a visit to France on Wednesday for talks with counterpart Nicolas Sarkozy and Prime Minister Francois Fillon. One of the main topics is expected to be Ankara's EU bid, which Sarkozy opposes. (Hurriyet, AFP - 06/10/09)
